PURPOSE:
Deliver alerts through multiple channels: webhooks, Slack, Discord, desktop notifications, and Agent Mail integration.

CHANNELS (from plan Section 8.1):

1. TUI HIGHLIGHT (MVP - already in Alerts MVP)
- Visual highlighting in TUI
- Sound alerts (optional, configurable)

2. FILE OUTPUT (MVP - already in Alerts MVP)
- Write to alerts.jsonl file
- Enables external tool integration

3. WEBHOOK
- POST JSON to configurable URL
- Support custom headers (auth tokens)
- Retry with exponential backoff

4. SLACK
- Slack incoming webhook integration
- Format messages with blocks for rich display
- Thread replies for updates

5. DISCORD
- Discord webhook integration
- Embed formatting for rich display

6. AGENT MAIL
- Send alert as mcp_agent_mail message
- Thread per alert for updates
- Tag with alert metadata

7. DESKTOP NOTIFICATIONS
- Use system notification APIs
- macOS: osascript/notification center
- Linux: notify-send or D-Bus

8. EMAIL (stretch goal)
- SMTP integration
- Template-based formatting

CHANNEL CONFIGURATION:
[alert_channels]

[alert_channels.slack]
enabled = true
webhook_url = "https://hooks.slack.com/..."
min_severity = "warning"

[alert_channels.webhook]
enabled = true
url = "https://my-service.com/alerts"
headers = { "Authorization" = "Bearer ${VC_WEBHOOK_TOKEN}" }
min_severity = "critical"

[alert_channels.desktop]
enabled = true
min_severity = "critical"

[alert_channels.agent_mail]
enabled = true
recipient = "HumanOperator"
min_severity = "warning"

DATA MODEL:
CREATE TABLE alert_delivery_log(
    id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    alert_id TEXT NOT NULL,
    channel_type TEXT NOT NULL,
    delivered_at TIMESTAMP,
    status TEXT,  -- pending, delivered, failed
    error_message TEXT,
    retry_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0
);

IMPLEMENTATION:
pub trait AlertChannel: Send + Sync {
    fn name(&self) -> &str;
    async fn deliver(&self, alert: &Alert) -> Result<(), ChannelError>;
    fn supports_severity(&self, severity: Severity) -> bool;
}

pub struct ChannelManager {
    channels: Vec<Box<dyn AlertChannel>>,

    pub async fn deliver_all(&self, alert: &Alert) -> Vec<DeliveryResult> {
        let futures = self.channels.iter()
            .filter(|c| c.supports_severity(alert.severity))
            .map(|c| c.deliver(alert));
        join_all(futures).await
    }
}

